description:
Install the OpenTelemetry Node.js SDK packages required for emitting traces, metrics, and logs to the Aspire Dashboard.

## Packages to Install
```bash
npm install @opentelemetry/sdk-node \
  @opentelemetry/api \
  @opentelemetry/auto-instrumentations-node \
  @opentelemetry/exporter-trace-otlp-grpc \
  @opentelemetry/exporter-metrics-otlp-grpc \
  @opentelemetry/resources \
  @opentelemetry/semantic-conventions
```

## Why These Packages
- `@opentelemetry/sdk-node`: Core SDK for Node.js
- `@opentelemetry/api`: API for creating custom spans
- `@opentelemetry/auto-instrumentations-node`: Auto-instrument HTTP, Fastify, etc.
- `@opentelemetry/exporter-*-otlp-grpc`: Export to Aspire Dashboard via OTLP/gRPC

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] All packages installed without conflicts
- [ ] TypeScript types available for all packages
- [ ] No breaking changes to existing dependencies

Configure and initialize OpenTelemetry SDK at backend startup, before Fastify server starts.

## Create src/telemetry.ts
```typescript
import { NodeSDK } from '@opentelemetry/sdk-node';
import { getNodeAutoInstrumentations } from '@opentelemetry/auto-instrumentations-node';
import { OTLPTraceExporter } from '@opentelemetry/exporter-trace-otlp-grpc';
import { OTLPMetricExporter } from '@opentelemetry/exporter-metrics-otlp-grpc';
import { Resource } from '@opentelemetry/resources';
import { ATTR_SERVICE_NAME } from '@opentelemetry/semantic-conventions';

const sdk = new NodeSDK({
  resource: new Resource({
    [ATTR_SERVICE_NAME]: process.env.OTEL_SERVICE_NAME || 'agent-ops-backend',
  }),
  traceExporter: new OTLPTraceExporter({
    url: process.env.OTEL_EXPORTER_OTLP_ENDPOINT || 'http://localhost:4317',
  }),
  metricReader: new OTLPMetricExporter({
    url: process.env.OTEL_EXPORTER_OTLP_ENDPOINT || 'http://localhost:4317',
  }),
  instrumentations: [getNodeAutoInstrumentations()],
});

export function initTelemetry() {
  sdk.start();
  process.on('SIGTERM', () => sdk.shutdown());
}
```

## Update src/index.ts
Import and call `initTelemetry()` BEFORE creating Fastify instance.

## Environment Variables (auto-injected by Aspire)
- OTEL_SERVICE_NAME
- OTEL_EXPORTER_OTLP_ENDPOINT

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] Telemetry initializes without errors
- [ ] HTTP requests appear as traces in Aspire Dashboard
- [ ] Graceful shutdown on SIGTERM

Refactor ObservabilityService to emit OpenTelemetry spans in addition to SQLite traces. Keep SQLite for domain-specific aggregation queries.

## Approach: Dual Output
1. **OpenTelemetry spans** → Aspire Dashboard visualization
2. **SQLite traces** → Domain queries (cost summaries, tool stats)

## Changes to ObservabilityService

### Add tracer instance
```typescript
import { trace, SpanKind, SpanStatusCode } from '@opentelemetry/api';

const tracer = trace.getTracer('agent-ops');
```

### Modify recordTrace() to emit OTEL span
```typescript
async recordTrace(trace: Omit<NewTrace, 'id' | 'timestamp'>): Promise<Trace> {
  // Emit OTEL span
  const span = tracer.startSpan(trace.eventType, {
    kind: SpanKind.INTERNAL,
    attributes: {
      'agent.worker_id': trace.workerId ?? undefined,
      'agent.work_item_id': trace.workItemId ?? undefined,
      ...flattenData(trace.data),
    },
  });
  span.end();

  // Also write to SQLite for queries
  // ... existing SQLite insert logic ...
}
```

### Add helper for custom spans
```typescript
startAgentSpan(name: string, workerId: string): Span {
  return tracer.startSpan(name, {
    attributes: { 'agent.worker_id': workerId },
  });
}
```

## What to Keep in SQLite
- getCostSummary() - domain-specific aggregation
- getToolCallStats() - per-tool breakdown
- getSystemMetrics() - worker aggregations
- getTraceStatsByEventType() - event distribution

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] All trace events appear in Aspire Dashboard
- [ ] SQLite queries still work for aggregations
- [ ] Tool calls show as child spans of agent operations
- [ ] Errors have proper OTEL status codes
